# Product Rule — What We Are Building

We are building a Kubernetes-native SaaS platform for creating, testing, deploying, and managing multi-functional AI agents and AI-powered apps.

## Product goals
- Local-first creation experience
- Cloud SaaS for project management and deployment
- Deploy agents/apps to Kubernetes
- Expose deployments through Kong
- Support Oracle Cloud as the primary infrastructure target
- Support a local companion app integrated with OpenClaw for local preview/testing

## Core product capabilities
- Create agents and apps
- Configure models, tools, secrets, environments, runtime profiles
- Test locally
- Sync local projects to cloud
- Deploy to Kubernetes
- Publish endpoints/apps behind Kong
- Observe deployment status, logs, and runtime health

## What is out of scope for MVP
- Marketplace
- Full no-code workflow marketplace
- Enterprise SSO
- Multi-region failover
- Arbitrary unrestricted code execution
- Publicly exposed raw OpenClaw gateways
- Complex plugin ecosystem

## Product language
Use these terms consistently:
- "Studio" = builder UI
- "Control Plane" = SaaS backend
- "Runtime Plane" = deployed workloads in Kubernetes
- "Deployment" = a versioned runtime release
- "Project" = top-level user workspace object
- "Agent" = AI behavior-first runtime
- "App" = user-facing application/runtime
- "Environment" = dev/staging/prod context
- "Route" = public or internal endpoint exposed via Kong

## Non-goals
Do not position the product as merely a clone or branded fork of another app.
This is a new platform with local-first authoring and cloud-native deployment.
